{
  "stem": "10572.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was disappointing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But at the same time, having watched the political situation in Germany and the economic situation in Germany, I often try to ask myself, if I was not Jewish, would I be tempted by this Hamelin pipe--",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pied Piper.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Would I have caved in and said, you know, maybe-- maybe I would have been a Nazi, too.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and of course, I thought that at the time-- before the unbelievable criminal activities the Nazis started.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, I would have said at-- at the time when he moved in, and he built autobahn, and he reduced the unemployment, and he rejuvenated the economic situation in Germany-- and--",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never-- I never-- with the exception of the anti-Semitism that I referred to at the European Fashion Academy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were Nazis in my group there, in my class, who made it tough.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But fortunately, I think in all of this time, I was old enough or I was maybe mature enough that I could evaluate these things for what they really were.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And maybe--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That-- that here with these primitive souls who didn't know what anti-Semitism was all about and why they were anti-Semites or why they were Nazis.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And let me go back quite a bit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In 1934-- in 1933 and '34, when we were in Dresden, I belonged to a youth group.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we came up with an idea-- I thought at that time was a fantastic idea.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Instead of having the yellow spot put on us as a sign of-- of shame, we developed a medal that was a yellow circle.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And for those who excelled in our youth group would get this yellow spot as an award.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we would say to them, wear it with pride.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They cannot defame us, and they cannot degrade us unless we degrade ourselves.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was, at that time, I thought, a kind of terrific morale booster for us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And maybe this attitude toward the yellow [NON-ENGLISH], that we turned it into a positive-- was a reflection of our youthful idealism, our naivete, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it helped us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I think we became more mature faster through these pressures that were working on us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Until they-- and-- and as I look back and try to answer your question, I did not ever suffer from unbearable anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But when-- when this thing happened to us in-- in May 1938, and we liquidated our downtown location, and took our workshop into our home and continued to-- continued our custom-made-- and had one designer and had maybe 15 loyal workers that stayed with us.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "None.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had among those only one Nazi.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Among-- among the 50 coat-makers, we had only one that we knew was a Nazi.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I believe he was from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he couldn't speak German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] But he always talked about the-- in-- in his funny dialect, that the Germans cannot have their own Fuhrer.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They have to bring him from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, he felt there was a bond between him and-- and Hitler.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was not made very, very welcome and happy in our workshop.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "All the other workers somehow had a distance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in-- in-- in-- in-- in the summer of 1938, I started to do some very serious soul-- soul-searching and-- and thinking of how we could get out of this dead-end street.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one day, my brother-in-law, the fellow who had gone to Atlantic City on his honeymoon-- a brother-in-law that I was not particularly fond of-- told me facetiously that his father's-- his-- his father had a chauffeur who drove him in a very elegant limousine all over the-- all over Germany.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were-- and this chauffeur had gotten a visit from a friend of his who was driving very wealthy American with her three daughters through Europe.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he had stopped in Hildesheim to say hello to Julius, this chauffeur.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my brother-in-law, who was teasing me at the same time about my consistent refusal of thinking in terms of emigration, but saw this change in me, and said, I'll give you a tip.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why don't you marry one of these girls that came yesterday with this American woman?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's how you can get to America.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because we didn't have any relatives in America.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't have any contacts here.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I didn't know how I could possibly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and he was sarcastic when he said it to me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I turned-- again, turned this negative into a positive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And said, you know?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Let me see.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Where do they go from here?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they went to the Harz Mountains where I used to go skiing, in Braunlage.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I called every hotel in Braunlage.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
